#ROOMS
#792
@@yWindswept Desert Edge@@N~
@@yYou stand at the edge of a vast, merciless desert that seems to stretch beyond the bounds of the world. The sand stretches endlessly in all directions beneath a scorching sun that offers no mercy, turning the sky to shades of pale orange and searing white. Ancient ruins protrude from dunes to the south, their weathered stone architecture suggesting once-grand structures now claimed by time and sand. To the north, a narrow canyon opens like the maw of some colossal beast, its sheer walls carved by millennia of wind and rare water. The air shimmers with heat in visible waves, distorting everything beyond arm's reach into a rippling mirage. Your skin feels the assault of the sun even through clothing, and each breath brings scorching air that parches mouth and throat. The wind is constant, carrying abrasive sand that stings exposed skin. Far in the distance, you can make out the faint shapes of more ruins rising from the dunes, the remnants of a once-mighty civilization now buried beneath centuries of shifting sand.@@N

