#793
@@yShifting Dune Ridge@@N~
@@yTowering sand dunes rise and fall like the frozen waves of an ancient sea locked in a moment of eternal motion. The ridge winds northward in a serpentine path, constantly changing as sand shifts in the ever-present wind. Loose sand beneath your feet gives way treacherously with each step, making progress difficult and exhausting. The slope of the dunes suggests ages of wind erosion, sculpting the sand into shapes of impossible beauty and terrible desolation. The horizon wavers and dances in the heat, revealing and concealing distant shapes that might be ruins, mirages, or delusions brought on by the punishing sun. When you look behind, your footprints are already being erased by the wind, as if your very presence is being denied by the desert itself. The dunes stretch on endlessly, each crest revealing only more dunes beyond, an infinity of sand and heat.@@N

