#794
@@ySand-Choked Trail@@N~
@@yAn ancient trade route runs east-west through the desert, now choked with centuries of accumulated sand. The original paving stones, once arranged in a careful mosaic pattern, are barely visible beneath deep drifts of fine golden sand. Faint wagon ruts mark the path, worn deep by countless merchants and their caravans before the desert claimed this land. In places where the wind has scoured the sand away, you can see the skilled stonework beneath—a testament to the craftsmen who built this road in an age when Akh'enet was not a tomb but a thriving center of civilization. The path appears to have connected distant oases once, navigating a route through the worst of the desert heat. Those oases are now buried and forgotten, if they ever truly existed at all. The trail itself is still relatively passable for those determined enough to follow it, though the sand constantly threatens to completely obscure the ancient way. Occasionally, half-buried artifacts emerge from the sand—broken pottery, corroded coins, and stranger objects of unknown purpose.@@N

