#797
@@yScorched Earth Flat@@N~
@@yThis barren expanse of blackened earth stretches endlessly in all directions, offering little cover or shelter from the relentless sun. The ground is deeply cracked and broken into irregular polygonal patterns, as if the very earth has been baked hard enough to split and fracture. Dark stains cover the cracked surface—perhaps from ancient fires, perhaps from substances better left unidentified—creating a surface that looks diseased and wronged. The heat here is almost visible, shimmering and rippling across the blackened earth in waves so intense they make the air itself shimmer like liquid glass. The effect is mesmerizing and deadly—the illusion of water where there is only infinite desolation. The temperature is noticeably higher here than in surrounding areas, as if the dark earth absorbs and radiates the sun's punishment back toward the sky. No vegetation grows here, no creature ventures here willingly. Even the wind seems reluctant to blow across this forsaken place.@@N

