#798
@@yDust Devil Crossing@@N~
@@yA natural crossroads where dust devils frequently form in violent spirals that seem almost sentient. The ground is scoured smooth by countless small tornadoes that pass through this region with terrible regularity, creating distinct swirling patterns in the sand. The very air crackles with static electricity in a way that makes your skin prickle and the hair on your arms stand on end. Fine sand swirls constantly, moving with hypnotic precision even in moments between storms, never quite settling or coming to rest. The dust here moves with an intelligence and purpose that seems almost malevolent, as if the desert itself is breathing and calculating. The raw power of these natural phenomena is both awe-inspiring and deeply terrifying. You can feel the faint pressure of building charge in the air, and occasionally you glimpse a dust devil forming right before your eyes—a spinning column of air and sand rising hundreds of feet skyward.@@N

