#799
@@yMirage Pool@@N~
@@yA shimmering expanse on the horizon resolves into what appears to be water surrounded by a grove of gnarled palms—a traveler's most desperate hope. As you approach, the vision wavers and distorts, becoming less and less certain with each painful step forward. The trees are petrified, turned to stone by some ancient process that strips away all life, their forms frozen in tortured gestures as if crying out in despair. The 'water' you saw is merely the intense refraction of light through superheated air rising from the blackened earth—a mirage born from the desert's cruel mockery of mercy. Dry stone basins, long since emptied of precious water, remain as silent testimony to what once was, perhaps real oases that have been sealed by some curse. The very sight of this place is an instrument of psychological torture, offering false hope before revealing the terrible truth of the wasteland. No water has flowed here in living memory.@@N

