#800
@@yPetrified Grove@@N~
@@yOnce, a verdant forest grew here, providing shelter and life to countless creatures. Now only the stone remains—a silent testament to time's merciless passage. The petrified timber stands like ghostly sentinels, gray and brittle as bone, stretching upward in a desperate gesture frozen forever. The wood has been hollowed by countless centuries of transformation, leaving intricate crystalline patterns where once was living wood. Some massive trunks still stand upright, reaching toward a sky that never rains, their forms contorted as if in eternal agony. Others lie scattered like fallen giants across the petrified forest floor, broken and worn by wind and time beyond measure. The petrification is so complete and thorough that the trees have become harder than any bedrock, almost indestructible. Between the stone trees, sand drifts in carefully sculpted forms that almost seem intentional, as if the desert is creating monuments to the forest it destroyed.@@N

