#803
@@yDune Crest Overlook@@N~
@@yFrom the highest dune in this entire region, you can see for seemingly endless miles across the desert landscape. Your vantage point provides a commanding view of the world below. To the south, more ruins emerge from the sand in stages of decay and burial, their shapes gradually becoming more distinct as they rise higher from the dunes. To the east, a canyon of impressive proportions cuts through distant dunes, its walls creating sharp shadows that mark its depth and danger. To the west, a vast and unbroken expanse of trackless desert stretches to the horizon where sky and sand blur into one another beyond distinction. The wind at this height is stronger and more relentless than below, whistling past with mournful sound. The view is simultaneously beautiful and absolutely soul-crushing in its immensity. You are tiny in the presence of such scale, a mere speck of consciousness lost in an ocean of sand.@@N

