#805
@@yRaider Ambush Point@@N~
@@yScattered bones and broken weapons litter this sandy area in testimony to the violence that has unfolded here repeatedly. The remains of past victims and fallen bandits lie half-buried beneath shifting sand, their original arrangement lost to time. Some bones are old and bleached white, others newer and still bearing dried tissue and sinew. Weapons lie broken and twisted—swords shattered from violent impact, shields cracked and splintered, spears bent at agonizing angles. The sand itself seems darker in places, stained by the dried blood of countless conflicts that have occurred at this cursed location. The smell of death still lingers faintly despite years and decades of exposure to wind and sun, a perfume of decay that warns of danger. The area shows clear signs of regular use as an ambush site—scattered rocks form crude hiding places, and the depression of the terrain provides natural defensive positions. This is ground soaked in violence and suffering.@@N

