#807
@@bBazaar Entrance Ramp@@N~
@@bA long ramp of precisely cut stone descends steeply into shadow and cool darkness. The entrance to the buried city lies far below, and you can feel the draw of the descent before you even commit to it. The ramp's edge is worn smooth by thousands of footsteps across countless centuries of use, each step by a merchant or pilgrim adding its wear to the eternal stone. The air grows noticeably cooler as you descend, a welcome respite from the furnace heat of the surface, smelling of deep stone dust and the irreplaceable aroma of great age. The walls alongside the ramp are carved with protective wards and inscriptions in the ancient language of Solahr—prayers for safe passage and prosperity for those who travel below. The stone beneath your feet is slightly slippery with age and mineral deposits. Darkness grows deeper with each downward step, swallowing light until you are descended into a world where the sun never reaches.@@N

